        public boolean needSuspend()
        Description copied from interface: SuspendibleActivity
        The method is invoked by the engine right after the activity is executed, to determine whether to put the activity instance in waiting status. Not all suspendible activities need to be suspended. For example, asynchronous process invocation, event wait when the event is already arrived, etc.

      • processOtherMessage

        protected void processOtherMessage(String messageString)
                            throws ActivityException
        This method is invoked to process a received event (other than task completion). You will need to override this method to customize processing of the event. The default method does nothing. The status of the activity after processing the event is configured in the designer, which can be either Hold or Waiting. When you override this method, you can optionally set different completion code from those configured in the designer by calling setReturnCode().
        Parameters:
        messageString - the entire message content of the external event (from document table)
        Throws:
        ActivityException

        public final boolean resume(InternalEvent event)

      • resumeWaiting

        public final boolean resumeWaiting(InternalEvent event)
                            throws ActivityException
        This method is made final for the class, as it contains internal logic handling resumption of waiting. It re-register the event waits including waiting for task to complete. If any event has already arrived, it processes it immediately. Customization should be done with the methods #processOtherMessage(String, String) and #registerWaitEvents().

      • processTaskCallRequest

        protected String processTaskCallRequest(String request)
        This method is invoked when the task instance makes a call to the engine through the method callEngine() of the task manager. The argument request is the request message of callEngine(). This method is intended to be overridden to do things like recording the request message in some variables or documents and returning a completion code to transition to appropriate activities. The method does not handle response, as that will be handled by processTaskCallResponse() after the process transitions back to the activity. The default method does nothing and return "Callback" as the completion code.
        Parameters:
        request -
        Returns:
        completion code

      • processTaskCallResponse

        protected String processTaskCallResponse()
        This method is used during processing callEngine(), task manager calls to the engine. It is invoked when the process instance transitions back to the task activity (which should be in hold status) and the method should return a response message which will be received by the task manager as the return value of the method callEngine(). The default method does nothing and returns "", and it is expected that the application will override this method to return appropriate response message.
        Returns:
        the response message which will be the return value of the task manager method callEngine().
